The paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques for fence removal, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning methods, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The optimization framework used in the paper involves sparsity and regularization, which are common techniques in mathematical modeling and optimization (cs.MM). The paper also deals with motion estimation, which is a common problem in graphics and visualization (cs.GR). Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm for processing images of dynamic scenes, which involves tracking and motion estimation, and is related to robotics and automation (cs.RO).
